          {
            "text": "Logic  ️",
            "note": "is the systematic study of the form of arguments  a valid argument is one where there is a specific relation of logical support between the assumptions of the argument and its conclusion   the validity of an argument is determined by its logical form, not by its content",
            "nodes": [
              {
                "text": "Computability theory  ️",
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "text": "Lambda calculus  ️",
                    "note": "is a formal system in mathematical logic for expressing computation based on function abstraction and application using variable binding and substitution  it is a universal model of computation that can be used to simulate any single-taped Turing machine   it consists of constructing lambda terms and performing reduction operations on them",
